HEADWORD: Dite
<hw>Dite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Dight</er>.]</ety> <def>To prepare for action or use; to make ready;
to dight.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His hideous club aloft he <qex>dites</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diterebene</ent>⟦br⟧
